text.__SUMMARY__: Psilocybe thaiduplicatocystidiata is a species of psilocybin mushroom in the family Strophariaceae. Found in Chiang Mai University Park (Chiang Mai Province, Thailand), where it grows on soil with rotting dung, it was described as new to science in 2012. The specific epithet thaiduplicatocystidiata refers to its dimorphic pleurocystidia and cheilocystidia, and to Thailand.
